article.description: James Kelly had 16 points and 14 rebounds, and Marshall won its first game with an 82-76 victory over Eastern Illinois in the Global Sports Classic on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Marshall beats Eastern Illinois 82-76 for first win
article.linkText: Marshall beats Eastern Illinois 82-76 for first win
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. -- James Kelly had 16 points and 14 rebounds, and Marshall won its first game with an 82-76 victory over Eastern Illinois in the Global Sports Classic on Wednesday night. Kelly had his second consecutive double-double. Ryan Taylor scored 22 points on 7-of-13 shooting to lead Marshall (1-6). C.J. Burks added 19 points with four assists and three steals. Trae Anderson scored a career-high 31 points for Eastern Illinois (2-5). Burks made a layup to stretch Marshall's lead to 70-53 with eight minutes remaining. Casey Teson and A.J. Riley made back-to-back 3-pointers to spark a 17-5 surge to pull Eastern Illinois to 75-70 with two minutes left. Anderson scored three layups, Marshall made only 5 of 10 free throws, and the Thundering Herd led 80-76 with 26 seconds to play. Taylor split another pair of free throws, and Stevie Browning forced a turnover and made a free throw to seal it.
